I want to elaborate on @Demi-Lune&#39;s answer a bit. I don&#39;t think there is a way you can get around creating a `MyData` instance, modifying that, and returning it from your chain methods. The whole reason that this sort of thing works in the first place is that all of your chain methods belong to the same class, and they return an instance of that class.

For example, `str.swapcase`, `str.zfill` and `str.replace` are all a part of `str`, and they all return `str`s.

